I would like to reiterate that I am not composed of brainless matter. I have simply chosen to reject my humanity; I have chosen to indulge in an elevated mindset as opposed to the mere herd mentality shared by the masses. This is a momentous decision, not to transgress ethical standards and become a monster of sorts,  but rather to enlighten myself with the roots of our lineage. Evolution and its shadowy path cannot restrain the sheer will exhibited by my soul. If I must regress to become the guiding light of the tumultuous book in which our species etch their tales, then so be it. After all, what is the loss of one man's present in relation to the futures of many? Thus, these complex factors have led me to what you may see as illogical behavior. What the common mind sees as irrational is no more than sense to the brilliant. Why must one see in order to pace themselves forward and why must one move aside for the relatively defined principles of right or left. I say we press onwards, to let the others make way for our illuminating path, or else to brace for the certain physical and psychological impacts that only genius can comprehend. I may have lost my mind, fallen victim to the lurking fears of rejection and ostracization, but I believe that I have simply become a monke.
